<h3>Service <code>var_abs</code></h3>
<p>Set the absolute value of a variable or setpoint.
If <code>value</code> is not defined, it is assumed to be 0.
If <code>unit_of_measurement</code> is not defined, it is assumed to be <code>native</code>.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Service data attribute</th>
<th>Optional</th>
<th>Description</th>
<th>Values</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>address</code></td>
<td>No</td>
<td><a href="#lcn-addresses">LCN address</a></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>variable</code></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Variable name</td>
<td><a href="#variables-and-units">VARIABLE</a>, <a href="#variables-and-units">SETPOINT</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>value</code></td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Variable value</td>
<td><em>any positive number</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>unit_of_measurement</code></td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Variable unit</td>
<td><a href="#variables-and-units">VAR_UNIT</a></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Example:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">service: var_abs
data:
  address: myhome.0.7
  variable: var1
  value: 75
  unit_of_measurement: %
</code></pre>
<div class='note'>
  Ensure that the LCN module is configured properly to provide acces to the defined variable.
  Otherwise the module might show unexpected behaviors or return error messages.
</div>
